<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="184" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,356,813]" pageId="5" pageNumber="184">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,607,632]" pageId="5" pageNumber="184">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[322,575,607,632]" pageId="5" pageNumber="184" refId="ref4664" refString="Robinson, G. S., Tuck, K. &amp; Shaffer, M. (1994) A Field Guide to the Smaller Moths of South-East Asia. Malaysian Nature Society, Kuala Lumpur, 309 pp." type="book">
Robinson 
<emphasis box="[437,494,608,632]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="184">et al.</emphasis>
(1994)
</bibRefCitation>
suggested that 
<taxonomicName authority="(Meyrick)" authorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[750,1103,607,632]" class="Insecta" family="Cosmopterigidae" genus="Ascalenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoracista">
<emphasis box="[750,982,608,632]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="184">Ascalenia thoracista</emphasis>
(Meyrick)
</taxonomicName>
is widespread throughout the Indo-Australian Region. 
<bibRefCitation box="[431,589,644,668]" pageId="5" pageNumber="184" refId="ref4165" refString="Koster, S. (2010) Order Lepidoptera, family Cosmopterigidae. Arthropod fauna of the UAE, 3, 532 - 551." type="journal article">Koster (2010)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[772,918,644,668]" class="Insecta" family="Cosmopterigidae" genus="Ascalenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoracista">
<emphasis box="[772,918,644,668]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="184">A. thoracista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses the thorn-like extension on the free part of the tergite VIII, similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Koster" authorityYear="2010" box="[544,697,680,704]" class="Insecta" family="Cosmopterigidae" genus="Gisilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gielisi">
<emphasis box="[544,697,680,704]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="184">Gisilia gielisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We examined 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[879,1026,680,704]" class="Insecta" family="Cosmopterigidae" genus="Ascalenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoracista">
<emphasis box="[879,1026,680,704]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="184">A. thoracista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and found that it shares the abovementioned features of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kasy" authorityYear="1968" box="[407,483,716,740]" class="Insecta" family="Cosmopterigidae" genus="Gisilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[407,483,716,740]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="184">Gisilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the female genitalia. Therefore, the species 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[1020,1134,716,740]" class="Insecta" family="Cosmopterigidae" genus="Ascalenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoracista">
<emphasis box="[1020,1134,716,740]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="184">thoracista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kasy" authorityYear="1968" box="[1329,1405,716,740]" class="Insecta" family="Cosmopterigidae" genus="Gisilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1329,1405,716,740]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="184">Gisilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in this study. An unnamed species of 
<taxonomicName box="[547,657,752,776]" class="Insecta" family="Cosmopterigidae" genus="Ascalenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[547,657,752,776]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="184">Ascalenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[781,927,752,776]" class="Insecta" family="Cosmopterigidae" genus="Ascalenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoracista">
<emphasis box="[781,927,752,776]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="184">G. thoracista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[1205,1269,752,775]" name="Japan" pageId="5" pageNumber="184">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation pageId="5" pageNumber="184" refId="ref3887" refString="Hirowatari, T., Matsui, S., Takagi, M., Nasu, Y. &amp; Ueda, K. (2012) Lepidoptera emerged from nests of the Bull-headed Shrike in Minamidaitojima, Japan. Lepidoptera Science, 63, 107 - 115." type="journal article">
Hirowatari 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="184">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[257,411,788,813]" pageId="5" pageNumber="184" refId="ref4398" refString="Kuroko, H. (2013) Cosmopterigidae. In: Hirowatari, T., Nasu, Y., Sakamaki, Y. &amp; Kishida, Y. (Eds.), The Standard of Moths in Japan. Vol. III. Gakken Education Publishing, Tokyo. pp 253 - 261." type="book chapter">Kuroko 2013</bibRefCitation>
). It is very likely that this species also belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kasy" authorityYear="1968" box="[955,1031,788,812]" class="Insecta" family="Cosmopterigidae" genus="Gisilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[955,1031,788,812]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="184">Gisilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
